            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "All the ftplugins prepend `silent!` to unmapping, except for\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c7d4a77ff9040c8b242f9d12a98472fe6217328c/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua#L85\nand\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c7d4a77ff9040c8b242f9d12a98472fe6217328c/runtime/ftplugin/gitrebase.vim#L45.\n\n\nnvim fails to change filetype and unmap in case of help:\n\n```\necho 'vim:ft=help' | nvim --clean -\n:nmap g==\n\" n  g==         *@<Lua 84: /tmp/nvim.CcX1Ip/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:72>\n:set ft=\n:set ft?\n\"   filetype=help\n:nmap g==\n\" n  g==         *@<Lua 83: /tmp/nvim.CcX1Ip/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:72>\n```\n\neven if `sil!` is prepended, say\n```diff\n--- a/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua\n+++ b/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua\n@@ -84,3 +84,3 @@ end, { buffer = true })\n vim.b.undo_ftplugin = (vim.b.undo_ftplugin or '')\n-  .. '\\n exe \"nunmap <buffer> gO\" | exe \"nunmap <buffer> g==\"'\n+  .. '\\n sil! exe \"nunmap <buffer> gO\" | sil! exe \"nunmap <buffer> g==\"'\n vim.b.undo_ftplugin = vim.b.undo_ftplugin .. ' | call v:lua.vim.treesitter.stop()'\n```\n\nHowever, unsetting filetype of gitrebase does not raise E31, and change of filetype and unmapping are successful:\n\n```\necho '# vim:ft=gitrebase' | nvim --clean -\n:nmap <C-A>\n\" n  <C-A>       *@:<C-U><C-R>=v:count1<CR>Cycle<CR>\n:set ft=\n:set ft?\n\"  filetype=\n:nmap <C-A>\n\" No mapping found\n```",
